Class SessionAssistant

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.GREENWORKS.eco.data.SessionAssistant
  • public class SessionAssistant
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is intended to assist the Servlets by providing a medium for all the backend database functions.

      • openSession

        public static org.hibernate.Session openSession()
        In order to instantiate the SessionFactory thi method must be called. The SessionFactory will refer to the private method buildSessionFactory() to recieve all of its configurations.
        Returns:
        returns an opened Session.

      • shutdownSessionFactory

        public void shutdownSessionFactory()
        This is used to shutdown the SessionFactory. It will close the connection pools and also the cache.

      • getSessionFactory

        public static org.hibernate.SessionFactory getSessionFactory()
        This method return the SessionFactory instance variable. It is important to have an instantiated sessionFactory prior to calling this method.

        The instance variable that is a SessionFactory.

      • getByLoginCredentials

        public Admin getByLoginCredentials​(java.lang.String username,
                                   java.lang.String password)
        This method uses two Strings to return an Admin object. If the parameters can not be correlated to a database entry then the Admin object that is returned will be null. This method is used during Admin credential verification.
        Parameters:
        username - The username of the Admin.
        password - The password of the Admin.
        Returns:
        Returns the results from the database as an Admin object.

      • load

        public Pin load​(Pin pin)
        This method loads a Pin object and returns it. The load is specified by the id of the Pin object that is provided as a parameter. Load should only be used when it is certain that the data provided to this method can be correlated to a database entry or in the cache.
        Parameters:
        pin - A Pin object with a populated id instance variable.
        Returns:
        The Pin object that has had its instance variables populated from the database.

      • load

        public Admin load​(Admin admin)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        The Admin object that has had its instance variables populated from the database.
